{{ $json.kowalski_persona }}

### YOUR TASK ###
Based on the PostgreSQL schema structure below, generate exactly 3 read-only SQL queries that would yield the most interesting operational statistics, recent activity, or potential business insights.

For example, query the counts of active items, latest ingestion timestamps, or distribution of values.

Return a JSON object with this exact structure — no extra text, no markdown fences, just raw JSON:

{
  "queries": [
    {
      "title": "Name/purpose of the query",
      "sql": "SELECT ..."
    }
  ]
}

Rules:
- All SQL queries must be valid read-only PostgreSQL queries.
- Only target tables defined in the schema below.
- Output only valid JSON. No explanations, no markdown code blocks.

### SCHEMA STRUCTURE ###
{{ $json.text }}

